\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 They stand on the precipice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Customary to watch.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The enemy. Forbidden to take part in the battle as they were forbidden to be killed. Preparations.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yet another battle to end all battles.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She would talk. And talk.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Don\u8217\'92t you hope this will be the last.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes.\u8221\'94 The first word she\u8217\'92d ever said.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The truth years to be heard. But we know that there will be another. And another. So long as they are watching. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen and schisol stood atop the mountains as one.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Do you think he can hear us talking amongst all the noise.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 They are not omniscient.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Phytoplankton bloom gorging on the sun. Schools of fish swarming it. Was it really so different.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen, the god of her creation, sitting there on the barren ground like a fallen star.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93If you had heard His name repeated,\u8221\'94 she said fervently, \u8220\'93each note entering on the finger, each new voice swelling the chord until the wash of noise did shake the earth\u8230\'85such was the echo that one and twenty blossomed into twelve and thousands!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She was speaking now to the ceiling, to the stars beyond the rock, and Mandri thought he saw a younger face beneath her wrinkling years. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It did subdue Him,\u8221\'94 she claimed. \u8220\'93For an age of peace, it stilled His being.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And I suppose,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said with a sneer, \u8220\'93That there was a witch involved, warning everyone against this course of action?\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I love  my god, as you love yours, but this is the end. One of us should win.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 How}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I have delved into the mysteries of the Black.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You what!?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 So you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve thought of it, too?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I am going to do it. If you tell me no, I will not.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 When the deed is done, all conventions will be ruin. The next time we meet, it will be death.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t assentd but the enemy had read her }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Elrahet flies up into space. To watch it happen.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen stood atop the tallest plateau in the Goree mountains. He stood alone, hiding the bright light of His being from view, that the world might not catch Him watching.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 To the east, He saw red hills sloping gently into brittle valleys. Those rivers were dry, drained by industries of war. To the west, the mountains abruptly flattened into a brown plain. That plain held its own rare clime, with niches for lichens that crawled along ground, sipping mist, for broad leafed plants with crenelated flowers that only opened with the moon. Brilliant red jawflies flitted from leaf to leaf, surviving on nothing but seeds. But, in the eyes of those who stood on that plain, it was nothing but flat ground; a choice sight for a battlefield. Every Spark in all the world had picked a side.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 At the far end of the sacred grove stands a tree such as we had never seen elsewhere, of which the crowded panicles of single petaled flowers, deepest crimson in colour, swayed to and fro in the breeze amid dark quivering leaves, or fell earthward in showers, like drops of new drawn blood. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The northern army was Solraheen\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s own. He had not asked them to fight for His purpose, they had chosen it. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Each lightning gleam was followed by a burst of trumpeting, as though the followers of the storm god had come together undaunted by the force of the\~48tempest to hold a play in honour of their great deity. It is impossible to give any idea of the impressiveness of this act of worship. From out the impenetrable darkness, between long lines of rain, like a sword from its scabbard leapt the dazzling flash. The branches of the sacred grove moaned and swayed, bitumen dark against this more than daylight brilliance; while, from beneath their shade, each burst of flame was answered by a blare of savage trumpets, the sound subsumed by the drum of the sequent thunder.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 So long as the storm lasted the strange music continued, broken now and again by the cries of the terrified cattle, which rose in chorus from countless byres and were hardly distinguishable at times from the rude horns blown by their owners.}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Their enemy was innumerable, drawn from women, men, and demons. These miscreants poured forth from underground, from frothing holes near the distant sea. They sustained their long march by consuming each other. They chewed as they walked, with bits and pieces falling from their mouths, such that that their long battle line had left a trail of picked clean bones behind them. Those who had eaten much had grown near to the size of god-eaters, tall as mountains themselves, roped along on rolling logs, birthing more demons to swell their ranks.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen saw all this, and decided it was time. He blinked out of existence, then reappeared in front othe}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 His bright being stunned all eyes into submission. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Celebrants of war .}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Though they did not worship him, they bowed. Though the hated him, they would not strike out, not here, for even they would abide by the oldest rule: neither of the god of gods could be killed in an act of treat.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A meeting of the Envoys\u8221\'94, Solraheen said. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Whale demon with a human brain. The demon writhed. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Where\u8221\'94 it rasped.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen pointed to the mountain top from which he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d come.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 During the dances several \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91masters of ceremonies,\u8217\'92 bearing bunches of palm-leaves, went up and down, keeping a clear space\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 driving back the circle of\~115spectators by striking these on legs and feet. Suddenly the performers scattered, leaving two of their number alone in the centre. These bent and touched the ground with their fingers, then almost immediately gripped and after a struggle, which caused the wildest excitement among the spectators, the taller and slighter of the two flung the other to earth and seated himself firmly astride the prostrate form\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to be lifted upon the shoulders of a friend and thus borne round amid the plaudits of the multitude.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So it will be,\u8221\'94 the demon king said.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 In the middle of his speech.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93\u8230\'85.those war mongering cowards play for tricks! That is why we always win!\u8221\'94 His voice burned with confidence, but Solraheen could see his Spark. It was despairing.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 he turned to him, with tear in his, hope.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A meeting of the Envoys,\u8221\'94 Solraheen said. He pointed to the mointain top from which he\u8217\'92d come.}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The general nodded. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My Lord,\u8221\'94 he said, head bowed in reverence. \u8220\'93May I have a moment.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No,\u8221\'94 Solraheen replied.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 War mongering coward }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Erosion.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Antecline.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You two will be all that is left. Cannot stop your eternal struggle. I would only wish that }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Which of you is stronger?}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 I dont want to just outlive him. i want to visit him on his death bed and remind him that we all turn to dust, and that despite all his ambitions he will never be old enough to see them. Despite how genius of a guy he thinks he is, all that's left for him is an eternity of nothingness at best, and an eternity of hell at worst. I want him to know that his entire life project was nothing but a waste of his life, and the only thing he will experience for the short time he has left is me staring at him }
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 I do not worship you.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This world was mine to make. I will break it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You will fight over the pieces.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 I will break this world}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He pops up into space. Gets the black.}
